<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="Cuba">
  <data key="d0">Cuba</data>
  <data key="d1">country</data>
  <data key="d2">Cuba is a country where protests are taking place, accompanied by arson and prolonged power outages.&lt;SEP&gt;Cuba is a country that has been subject to a U.S. oil blockade since January, and to which a Russian oil tanker is scheduled to deliver approximately 730,000 barrels of oil.&lt;SEP&gt;Cuba is the country targeted by U.S. tariffs, as it receives oil and petroleum products from other nations, which the United States seeks to penalize.&lt;SEP&gt;Cuba engaged in secret negotiations with the United States in Havana, with its leadership reportedly meeting with U.S. State Department officials and being urged to implement reforms amid economic decline.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a2c1fe6eec4b0d533b5269363a9c02da&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-26a0c741b3e720a0878cd12efde32ab3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a87bd5684f407f2900f544cd1ebd84b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e0fc3662465aeaa22012fc5b57b9ab2</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Куба\5.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Куба\6.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Куба\7.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Куба\8.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777504068</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="United States">
  <data key="d0">United States</data>
  <data key="d1">country</data>
  <data key="d2">United States is a country with which the president of Cuba has announced the beginning of negotiations.&lt;SEP&gt;United States is a country that has imposed an oil blockade on Cuba since January, authorized a Russian oil tanker to reach Cuba, and added Cuba to a list of countries prohibited from purchasing Russian oil.&lt;SEP&gt;The United States is the country implementing economic sanctions in the form of tariffs on nations that supply oil to Cuba, citing national security concerns.&lt;SEP&gt;United States conducted secret talks with Cuba in Havana for the first time in 10 years, proposing the lifting of trade embargo and access to Starlink satellite communication in exchange for democratic and economic reforms, release of political prisoners, and compensation for confiscated assets.&lt;SEP&gt;United States is referenced by Alexander Dugin as a foreign power seeking to establish a foothold in post-Soviet states.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a2c1fe6eec4b0d533b5269363a9c02da&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-26a0c741b3e720a0878cd12efde32ab3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a87bd5684f407f2900f544cd1ebd84b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e0fc3662465aeaa22012fc5b57b9ab2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c3304f520cd42cf6e6640f83b9b8f87c</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Куба\5.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Куба\6.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Куба\7.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Куба\8.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Ультра левые и ультра правые\10.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777504089</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Communist Party of Cuba">
  <data key="d0">Communist Party of Cuba</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Communist Party of Cuba is a political organization whose local offices have been set on fire by protesters in some cities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a2c1fe6eec4b0d533b5269363a9c02da</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Куба\5.txt</data>
