<edge source="Cuba" target="United States">
  <data key="d7">4.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The president of Cuba announced the beginning of negotiations with the United States.&lt;SEP&gt;United States has imposed an oil blockade on Cuba since January and prohibited Cuba from purchasing Russian oil.&lt;SEP&gt;The United States imposed tariffs on countries supplying oil to Cuba, framing the action as a measure to counter Cuba's threat to U.S. national security.&lt;SEP&gt;The United States conducted secret negotiations with Cuba in Havana, proposing the lifting of trade embargo and access to Starlink in exchange for democratic reforms, release of political prisoners, and compensation for assets seized after the 1959 Revolution.</data>
  <data key="d9">blockade,conditional proposal,diplomatic engagement,economic sanction,national security policy,negotiation,secret negotiation,trade restriction</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-a2c1fe6eec4b0d533b5269363a9c02da&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-26a0c741b3e720a0878cd12efde32ab3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a87bd5684f407f2900f544cd1ebd84b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e0fc3662465aeaa22012fc5b57b9ab2</data>
